reviews.text:
Another amazing hidden treasure in the heart of Mongkok. This was a restaurant chosen by the locals and they were spot on when they told we would love the food. 

I’ve been falling in love with food of late and Peking Garden was no exception. They have a large variety of dishes to serve and it’s pretty amazing how quick the service is. I don’t think I waited even for more than a couple of minutes before the next course came in. 

Reservations are preferred as is the case with most places during lunchtime in Hong Kong to cutdown the waiting time.
The quality and the quantity don't worth the price. Location is good though.
Great food. Service was acceptable. Restaurant was crowded and loud though, so harder to talk
All the dim sum are ordered on demand. Very tasty and authentic!
very bad service... bad food quality.... not fresh ... full of MSG ... MSG!!! stay away please !!! do yourself a favor!!

reviews.text: 食物很優質，價錢應該是很貴，不過其他人找數！🤭
首推，桂花拉糕，個人非常喜愛。

食物質素屬於中上，價錢也相等。
但醉雞的胸肉太“鞋”，須有待改進。
可以一試，有必吃點心，但漏單再補時，等的時間比較長。
食品精緻，道地北京風味，員工有禮、勤快。
